					<div class="business">
						<h2 class="title pt0">A global leading developer </h2>
						<p class="explain">Bringing together its ample experience in SOC projects, creative ideas, and topnotch construction capacity, Hyundai Development Company has displayed outstanding performance in total package development inking  energy plants, harbors and highways. The company has also been recognized in overseas markets, positioning itself as a global leading developer in urban development and energy plants.</p>

						<div class="img_box">
							<img src="/front/en/images/02business/img_abroad01.jpg" alt="Bangkhen Water Treatment Plant" />
						</div>

						<div class="hr"></div>

						<div class="txt_box">
							<p class="dark mb0">Bangkhen water treatment plant – The cornerstone of Hyundai Development Company’s South East Asia market penetration</p>
							<p class="light mt14">Following our successful entry into the Middle East market, Hyundai Development Company has also made inroads into the South East Asian market to participate in various SOC projects In particular, the Bangkhen water treatment plant is recognized for its technological excellence and has helped us expand our presence in the market. Completed in 1989 and based on Hyundai Development Company’s technology and construction capacity, the plant has grown into one of the most advanced green facilities in the region</p>
						</div>

						<div class="img_box">
							<img src="/front/en/images/02business/img_abroad02.jpg" alt="Gizan Cement Plant Project" />
						</div>

						<div class="hr"></div>

						<div class="txt_box">
							<p class="dark mb0">Gizan Cement plant project – The first overseas turn-key contract for Korean constructors</p>
							<p class="light mt14">Gizan cement plant project was the first ever turn-key construction project that a Korean company won in the overseas markets. It was also Hyundai Development Company’s first plant export and overseas project. The USD 127.2-million project, which took three years before its completion in January 1981, established the reputation of Hyundai Development Company in the Cement plant industry.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="img_box">
							<img src="/front/en/images/02business/img_abroad03.jpg" alt="Al-Jubail Refinery Complex I" />
						</div>

						<div class="hr"></div>

						<div class="txt_box">
							<p class="dark mb0">Al-Jubail Refinery complex – Cementing plant construction leadership in the middle East</p>
							<p class="light mt14">Hyundai Development Company won the USD 124.6-milliong Al-Jubail refinery complex project commissioned by Saudi Aramco. Paricipating in a consortium of the United States, Japan, France and Korea. Hyundai Development Company displayed our state-of-the-art capacity in construction and civil engineering . Commencing construction in August 1979 and completed in January 1981, the 250,000 barrels per day Al-Jubail refinery complex helped Hyundai Development Company secure a leading position in plant construction in the Middle East.</p>
						</div>

						<div class="img_box">
							<img src="/front/en/images/02business/img_abroad04.jpg" alt="Sunghi Perak Bridge, Teluk-Lumut Road, Perak" />
						</div>

						<div class="hr"></div>

						<div class="txt_box mb0">
							<p class="dark mb0">Sunghi Perak Bridge, Teluk-Lumut Road, Perak – Constructed using Free Cantilevering Method (FCM)</p>
							<p class="light mt14">Hyundai Development Company won the Perak Bridge and Connecting Road Construction Project commissioned by the Malaysian Public Works Department in 1986 and completed the project in 1989. The 1,154m Perak Bridge in Korea, is a representative bridge constructed using FCM. Hyundai Development Company was able to win reputation for technological prowess through this project, as the company completed the project with only 3-4mm margin of error.</p>
